    <note>Huang(2) Huan [18974] Both Fujian TZ, 150.14a (with radical 85 instead of 86 as generational indicator in mingzi) and San shanzhi, 32.42b identify him as a younger brother of Shiyong 18972], son of Jingyue [18968]. Xie's [18970] entry (q.v.) identifies Shiyong, Shican [18971] and Huan [18974] all as younger brothers, therefore a son of Jue(2) [18969], whereas all other sources identify Shiyong and Shican as sons of Jingyue. Based on generational name, I am assuming that Huan was a son of Jue(2) and younger brother of Xie and a cousin of Shican and Shiyong. I suspect the confusion may be owing to an adoption at some point.</note>
